#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "RipGrep"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:18
msgid ""
"`ripgrep` is a line-oriented search tool that recursively searches the "
"current directory for a _regex_ (regular expression) pattern. By default, "
"_ripgrep_ respects the rules of _gitignore_ and automatically skips hidden "
"files/directories and binaries. Ripgrep offers excellent support on Windows, "
"macOS and Linux, with binaries available for each release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install RipGrep from EPEL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:22
msgid ""
"In both Rocky Linux 8 and 9, you can install RipGrep from the EPEL. To do "
"this, install the `epel-release,` upgrade the system, and then install "
"`ripgrep.`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo dnf install -y epel-release\n"
"sudo dnf upgrade\n"
"sudo dnf install ripgrep\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install RipGrep using `cargo`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:32
msgid ""
"Ripgrep is software written in _Rust_ and is installable with the `cargo` "
"utility. Note, however, that `cargo` is not installed by the default "
"installation of _rust_ so you have to install it explicitly. If you run into "
"errors using this method, revert back to installing from the EPEL."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install rust cargo\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:38
msgid ""
"Once the necessary software is installed, we can install `ripgrep` with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "cargo install ripgrep\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:44
msgid ""
"The installation will save the `rg` executable in the `~/.cargo/bin` folder "
"which is outside the PATH, to use it at the user level we will link it to "
"`~/.local/bin/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s ~/.cargo/bin/rg ~/.local/bin/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "RipGrep Verification"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:52
msgid "At this point we can check that everything is okay with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rg --version\n"
"ripgrep 13.0.0\n"
"-SIMD -AVX (compiled)\n"
"+SIMD +AVX (runtime)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:61
msgid "RipGrep is needed for recursive searches with `:Telescope`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Lazygit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:65
msgid ""
"[LazyGit](https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit) is an ncurses-style "
"interface that allows you to perform all `git` operations in a more user-"
"friendly way. It is required by the _lazygit.nvim_ plugin. This plugin makes "
"it possible to use LazyGit directly from NvChad, it opens a floating window "
"from where you can perform all operations on your repositories, thus "
"allowing you to make all changes to the _git repository_ without leaving the "
"editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:67
msgid ""
"To install it we can use the repository for Fedora. On Rocky Linux 9 it "
"works perfectly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/additional_software.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo dnf copr enable atim/lazygit -y\n"
"sudo dnf install lazygit\n"
msgstr ""

